## Maintenance Record Rules

1. Record Creation
   - All required fields must be provided
   - Service date must be valid
   - Mileage must be positive
   - Cost must be non-negative
   - Service provider must be specified

2. Record Updates
   - Only admin can update records
   - Historical data cannot be modified
   - Future dates must be valid
   - Mileage must be increasing
   - Cost updates must be justified

3. Record Deletion
   - Only admin can delete records
   - Deletion must be logged
   - Related records must be handled
   - Backup must be maintained

4. Record Access
   - Users can view their car records
   - Admins can view all records
   - Sensitive data must be protected
   - Access must be logged

5. Data Validation
   - Dates must be in valid range
   - Mileage must be realistic
   - Costs must be reasonable
   - Descriptions must be meaningful
   - Service types must be valid

6. Maintenance Scheduling
   - Next service date must be future
   - Next service mileage must be higher
   - Reminders must be configurable
   - Notifications must be sent

7. Reporting
   - Cost reports must be accurate
   - History must be complete
   - Analytics must be meaningful
   - Export must be available
